\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 15, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104bye1665703174860.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bye1665703174860.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/bye1665703174860.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"bye1665703174860\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Builds the messages that are used in the disconnection protocol. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bye1665703174860__section_w2083ab1b5b1_w2084ab1b5_w2085ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d480180e49\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">SMTP security drivers</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bye1665703174860__section_dfh_4sp_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d480180e58\">Expected Input</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132404e1_d132405e1_d132406e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">Properties</code>,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">Parameters</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132407e1_d132408e1_d132409e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">InBuf</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">InDataLen</code>,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">InBufLen</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132410e1_d132411e1_d132412e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">DrvArea</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bye1665703174860__section_qvt_4sp_dwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d480180e88\">Expected Output</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132104e1_d132105e1_d132106e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBuf</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutDataLen</code>,\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">OutBufLen</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132107e1_d132108e1_d132109e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsg</code>, <code class=\"ph codeph\">ErrMsgLen</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132110e1_d132111e1_d132112e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">DrvArea</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bye1665703174860__section_w2086ab1b5b7_w2087ab1b5_w2088ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d480180e118\">Return Status</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132116e1_d132117e1_d132118e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_SUCCESS</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132119e1_d132120e1_d132121e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_ERROR</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"bye1665703174860__section_w2089ab1b5b9_w2090ab1b5_w2091ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d480180e134\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132125e1_d132126e1_d132127e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_CLOSEMSG</code> function is called\n        when the connection is to be closed. It builds the messages that are used in the\n        disconnection protocol. The function is called repeatedly with the server’s responses until\n        it indicates that the protocol is complete or has failed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"bye1665703174860__p_d132128e1_d132129e1_d132130e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_CLOSEMSG</code> is the counterpart of <code class=\"ph codeph\">USEC_OPENMSG</code>, which\n        provides more information about the way these functions should be used.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/njm1665702678320.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>USEC_OPENMSG</a><p>Prepares the messages that are to be sent to the server in order to carry out the initialisation and authentication protocol to establish a connection.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526304\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526304\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "USEC_CLOSEMSG Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 15, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Builds the messages that are used in the disconnection protocol. Use SMTP security drivers Expected Input Properties , Parameters InBuf , InDataLen , InBufLen DrvArea Expected Output OutBuf , OutDataLen , OutBufLen ErrMsg , ErrMsgLen DrvArea Return Status USEC_SUCCESS USEC_ERROR Description The USEC_CLOSEMSG function is called when the connection is to be closed. It builds the messages that are used in the disconnection protocol. The function is called repeatedly with the server’s responses until it indicates that the protocol is complete or has failed. USEC_CLOSEMSG is the counterpart of USEC_OPENMSG , which provides more information about the way these functions should be used. Related Links USEC_OPENMSG Prepares the messages that are to be sent to the server in order to carry out the initialisation and authentication protocol to establish a connection. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}